data.content:
Three breaking changes hit your code. Here's each one and the fix:

---

### 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` ŌĆö no longer accepts expression trees

The setter parameter changed from `Expression<Func<...>>` to `Func<...>`. Your manual expression tree won't compile. Replace with a simple lambda:

```csharp
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

No more `Expression.Lambda`/`Expression.Call` gymnastics needed.

---

### 2. Complex type column names ŌĆö now auto-uniquified & use full path

Two changes combined:

- **Sibling conflict**: `ShippingAddress.Street` and `BillingAddress.Street` previously silently shared one `Street` column ŌåÆ now EF appends a number (`Street`, `Street1`), which **breaks existing schemas**.
- **Nested path**: `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` previously mapped to `BillingAddress_City` ŌåÆ now maps to `Payment_BillingAddress_City`.

**Fix** ŌĆö pin column names explicitly via `HasColumnName`:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress, p =>
        p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("ShippingAddress_Street"));
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress, p =>
        p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_Street"));
});

// Nested: pin to the old convention if you have existing data
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>()
    .ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment)
    .ComplexProperty(p => p.BillingAddress)
    .Property(a => a.City)
    .HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City");   // old: excluded "Payment_"
```

Or generate a new migration and review the column renames carefully.

---

### 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` ŌĆö new `logCommandText` parameter

Every method gained a `string logCommandText` parameter (for redacted SQL logging).

```csharp
public class MyLogger : IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger
{
    public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
        IRelationalConnection connection,
        DbCommand command,
        DbContext context,
        Guid commandId,
        Guid connectionId,
        DateTimeOffset startTime,
        string logCommandText)        // ŌåÉ new parameter
    {
        // Use logCommandText for logging (constants are redacted)
        // Use command.CommandText for the actual executed SQL
    }
}
```

Update **all** method signatures on the interface (`CommandScalarExecuting`, `CommandReaderExecuted`, etc.) the same way.
